cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses improvements to the capsule network architecture for computer vision tasks, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the training of parameters in different capsule layers, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper proposes a novel architecture and discusses the effect of initialization methods, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper experiments with computer vision datasets, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible sub-category.
